A little update on my brothers @filip_and_liam . They are fighters and doing well. Liam still has his open fontanel and now hair is not growing over the hole so he has a slight bald spot on the top of his head. It gives him character. Filip is learning to adjust with his cleft palette and when he gets a little older around 1 years of age, he will need to undergo a couple surgeries to correct. The vet says that they would need to slice part of his hard palette and fold it down to his soft palette to cover the hole. It causes him to regurgitate when he eats and drinks and he has lots of mucus that comes from his nose. They are both doing well but just need to get lots of check ups and need to be monitored a lot. And of course need lots of love and bacon. Thanks for all your support and thank you to @chicagofrenchbulldogrescue for saving them.
